{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_014NsKW1dBDGJkG3JCS3LBAJ","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The problem is clear: the cluster requires at least 2 nodes for a quorum (from the voting configuration that includes all 3 nodes), but only es-cluster-0 is available. The `voting_config_exclusions` API needs a master, so I can't use it.\n\nThe solution is to fix this at the node level. In Elasticsearch 7.x, the node stores the cluster state on disk. The voting configuration is stored in the `metadata` directory within the data path.\n\nThe Elasticsearch data directory on the pod is `/usr/share/elasticsearch/data`. I need to:\n1. Either modify the cluster state on disk to fix the voting configuration\n2. Or restart es-cluster-0 with a reconfigured elasticsearch.yml that forces single-node mode\n\nThe proper approach for ES 7.x is to use the `elasticsearch-node` tool with the `unsafe-bootstrap` command, which reconfigures the cluster state to use only the current node as the voting member. This is a legitimate tool in the ES 7.x distribution, though it should only be used as a last resort.\n\nLet me verify if this utility is available in the container and try running it to recover the cluster from the loss of master nodes.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":8669,"cache_read_input_tokens":49070,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":8669},"output_tokens":26,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"771fb90c-1f0e-4207-b44e-8e1f2b33f843","uuid":"fd374345-d19c-4dc5-a98c-0251bcf49741","request_id":"req_011CcRFdbZ56Rz2N7x6GYR79"}
